<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-03-04T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-03-04T15:00:00-05:00" n="532" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d532">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">123EN3/523: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-03-04T15:00:00-05:00">March 4, 1937—3
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>68. Engert is departing from Addis Ababa on March 5 and instructions
                                have been issued to close the office entirely on March 31. Unless
                                you perceive some objection please advise the Foreign Office orally
                                and informally that we should be appreciative if it would continue
                                to furnish us, as has been done during recent months, with any
                                available information regarding welfare of American nationals in
                                Ethiopia.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>